Well-known South Africans send their condolences, following the passing of former UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan Annan died at a hospital in the Swiss capital, Bern, after a brief illness. The 80-year-old served as the seventh UN chief for almost 10 years from 1997-2006 and was awarded a Nobel Prize in 2001, which he shared with the UN. A statement shared by his Twitter account on Saturday described Annan as a “global statesman and deeply committed internationalist”.  READ MORE: 7 things you may have not known about Kofi Annan’s impressive career   READ MORE: Tutu, Ramaphosa and other world leaders mourn passing of Kofi Annan 